<br>
Example:  2 Monks have a tink bag to trade, we roll to see who trades.  Monk 1 wins and now has a bag with half the weight as the original bag he traded.<br>
<br>
That monk can then roll again on the tink bag, allowing him to possibly win back the bag he traded, however, he would then be rolling against all those rolling on the tink.<br>
<br>
This is an advantage for monks, not a disadvantage.  I hope that answers your question =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=windzer>Windzer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/22/02 1:22:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1035.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Monday February 25 6pm EST</span><hr size=1> I'm there, 52 wiz.<br>
